# Existing Codebase Rule — Dyad OSS Adaptation

This repository already contains the Dyad open-source codebase at the root.

We are not starting from scratch.
We must evolve the current codebase into a new product.

## Primary objective
Adapt the existing OSS codebase into a platform for:
- multi-functional AI agents/apps
- local-first building
- SaaS synchronization and deployment
- Kubernetes runtime deployment
- Kong-based exposure
- OpenClaw local integration

## Required working mode
Before creating new structures, always:
1. inspect the current repository structure
2. identify reusable modules/components
3. identify branding references
4. identify architecture assumptions from the existing app
5. propose an incremental migration plan

## Reuse policy
Prefer:
- refactoring
- extracting shared modules
- renaming existing modules
- extending existing app architecture

Avoid:
- replacing working code unnecessarily
- duplicating current capabilities in parallel folders
- introducing a second architecture that conflicts with the current root structure

## Migration principle
All major changes should follow:
- inspect
- map
- preserve reusable pieces
- isolate risky pieces
- refactor incrementally

## Required outputs when modifying the repo
Always state:
- what existing code is being reused
- what existing code is being replaced
- what existing code is being left untouched for now
- what new modules are introduced
